                                <p style="margin-top: 50px;">This dataset is a comprehensive collection of historical data of the 
                                    economic history library of the Ludwig Maximilians Universität of Munich, 
                                    meticulously curated for educational and research purposes. Explore a wide range of topics 
                                    and variables through our interactive table.
                                </p>
                                <p>The collection of this data accounts for diverse topics withing the period of the german empire 
                                    (1871-1945). The selection focused on data available for smaller units of observation, excluding 
                                    information that was only available at the empire level. Therefore, it contains mostly disaggregated
                                    statistics, which enables a finer and more detailed comprehension of the specific topics throughout
                                    the german territory.
                                </p>
